# SCSS Rules

## Foundation
- All styles in `<style lang="scss" scoped>` inside components
- Global styles only in `assets/styles/main.scss`
- Variables defined in `assets/styles/_variables.scss` — always use them, never hardcode values
- Mixins in `assets/styles/_mixins.scss`

## Variable usage
Always import and use variables:
```scss
// ✅
color: $color-primary;
font-size: $font-size-lg;
padding: $spacing-md;

// ❌
color: #6c63ff;
font-size: 18px;
padding: 24px;
```

## Naming: BEM
```scss
// Block
.project-card { }

// Element
.project-card__title { }
.project-card__tags { }
.project-card__image { }

// Modifier
.project-card--featured { }
.project-card--dark { }
```

## Nesting
- Max 3 levels deep — beyond that, extract a new block
- Use `&` for BEM elements and modifiers:
```scss
.project-card {
  padding: $spacing-md;

  &__title {
    font-size: $font-size-xl;
  }

  &--featured {
    border: 2px solid $color-primary;
  }
}
```

## Responsive
- Mobile-first
- Use breakpoint mixin from `_mixins.scss`:
```scss
.hero {
  font-size: $font-size-lg;

  @include breakpoint(md) {
    font-size: $font-size-xl;
  }
}
```

## DO NOT
- Don't write media queries inline without the mixin
- Don't use `!important` unless overriding third-party (add comment explaining why)
- Don't use `px` for font sizes — use variables or `rem`
- Don't duplicate variables — always check `_variables.scss` first
